OUR LOOK AT THE SCHOOL SYSTEM

Photo by Tiffany Lynn and Thoughts of Benjamin F. Bleacher iii

As all of our articles, these are our thoughts and our point of view. We are always learning and open to new perspectives. Our writings are written on a level that a three-year-old can understand them to a hundred and three years old.We hope to reach out to the massive. Thank you for your love and support. We appreciate every one of you. With that said here is our thoughts on the school system. "IT IS BROKEN". "IT IS A SLAVE SYSTEM". It makes our children study things that will never help them in the real world. It makes all of us do things around its schedule long after we have graduated. When we become parents now we need to take our children to school or arrange for them to get there.I am not anti-school. What I am is anti-wasting time by studying things that will not be useful out in the real world or make them feel less than for the fact that they might not understand. Spending years of their lives learning subjects like History, math, science, Spanish. All these subject are somewhat helpful. The question that is on our mind is. Why are we as a system not teaching: Self-love, proper nutrition, teamwork, communication and understanding skills, how to listen to hear what another is saying, Instead of listening to react, how to get to the root of our problems. How about having a class that brings each of our own unique gifts? With this solid foundation, the days after school will become more enjoyable. Math is needed and history is helpful for the fact in order to know where we are going we must understand where we came from.Will the day ever come when we stop wasting years of our children's live's and then setting them free out into the world without the proper mindset and skills to help them along their journeys? This is our responsibility future generations are counting on us. Unless for some reason we wish to see continue what has been happening in past generations. With more drop-outs, crime rate going up and prisons being filled up. Our children have no clue about the things that matter and we set the free to find it out in the world. #thoughtprovoking #school

Victory!!!! 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼 IBM severs ties with New York Blood Center (NYBC) after over 50 years until they take responsibility for the 66 chimps they abandoned and left to starve to death on an island in Liberia. NYBC experimented on over 500 chimps they bred in captivity for 30 plus years and then disposed of the surviving 66 chimps like trash. 😡😡😡 Luckily, animal activist groups and even compassionate Liberians have been helping take care of the chimps by supplying food and water.  Read article at http://theirturn.net/2017/05/08/ibm-condemns-new-york-blood-center/. Other large corporate partners like MetLife and Citigroup have also taken a stand against NYBC. Please continue to put pressure on NYBC and urge them to provide lifetime care for these chimps. Phone is 800-688-0900 or go to nybloodcenter.org to express your disappointment and concern. NYBC made a promise so let's make sure they keep it. These chimps deserve quality of life. #chimps #betrayal #animalexperimentation #NewYorkBloodCenter #shameonnewyorkbloodcenter #animalabuse #animalabandonment #responsibility #moralobligation #Repost @nyclass

Do you remember this ad? This was an anti smoking campaign from the late 80s or early 90s and I have never forgotten it. 
It appeals to our vanity so effectively. 'If what happened on your inside happened on your outside, would you still smoke?'
I WOULD LOVE TO ASK THE SAME THING ABOUT SELF TALK. 'If your non-serving thoughts did the same thing to your physical life as they do to your emotional/energetic life, would you keep ignoring them? Keep thinking them? Keep letting them run the show?'
Conversely, if clear, serving, productive, INTENTIONAL thoughts caused physical benefit at the same proportion that they cause emotional/spiritual benefit, would you try a little harder? 
It's a bit absurd that we care so much for what makes us LOOK healthy but we can neglect the things that truly make us healthy. ::::
If you had to wear your thoughts as words on your body, would you think the same thoughts? About yourself? About others? About life? ::::
Thanks, 1980s smoking ad. I'm still considering you :)
